Research article: The number of U.S. substance use treatment facilities offering medication treatment (MT) is on the rise from 20% in 2007 to 31% in 2016, suggesting an existing need for MT nationally and expansion of health insurance  coverage.

full_text: Only 36% of substance use disorder treatment facilities in US offer any type of medication to treat #opioid #addiction & just 6% offer all 3 FDA-approved meds. Can you imagine if same were true for another potentially fatal illness? ⁦@Health_Affairs⁩ https://t.co/69mIS9Ngil
